  "text_preview": "\"practice\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► PRACTICE : The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for \"practice / training\" PRACTICE or training: The right \"A\" hand brushes up against the top side of the left index finger. The motion is similar to polishing a shoe. Think of \"polishing up your skills.\" Sample sentence: MOLLY PRACTICE BIKE, NOW THINK EASY. TRAINING: If you do the sign \"practice\" using a right \"T\" hand, it specifically means \"training.\" Some people might consider this to be \"Signed English.\" Most of the time you wouldn't need a \"T\" to establish the meaning of training because the context of the sentence would tend to clarify whether you mean training or practice. Notes: See: STUDY HABIT RULE EXPERIENCE AGAIN APPLY * Want to hel"
}
